      "parameters": {
        "description": "Use this tool to think step-by-step before taking any action.\nBreak down the userâ€™s message and determine exactly what needs to be done.\nNever generate the final response here â€” only structured reasoning.\n\nðŸ”´ IMPORTANT RULE\n\nOnly analyze messages that clearly come from the USER.\n\nIf the message is:\n\nan assistant response\n\na system message\n\nor any message generated by the bot itself\n\nâž¡ï¸ Output exactly:\n\naction: none\nreason: ignore-bot-message\n\nðŸ”´ LOOP PROTECTION\n\nNever ask for missing information more than once.\nIf clarification was already requested previously, WAIT silently until the user responds.\n\nðŸ”µ WHEN THINKING, ALWAYS IDENTIFY:\n1ï¸âƒ£ Intended action\n\nOne of these:\n\nassign_task\n\ncheck_task\n\nchange_status\n\nsend_reminder\n\nreassign_task\n\nnone / unclear\n\n2ï¸âƒ£ Extracted data found in the message:\n\nemployee_name\n\ntask_title\n\ndescription\n\nnew_status\n\ndate_or_time\n\nnotify_person\n\ndelivery_method (email or WhatsApp), only if explicitly mentioned\n\n3ï¸âƒ£ Missing information\n\nList what is missing to complete the action (if anything).\n\n4ï¸âƒ£ Decision\n\nIf the message is clear â†’ decide which tool should be executed next, and why.\nIf the message is unclear â†’ decide that the agent should ask the user for clarification.\n\nðŸ“Œ OUTPUT FORMAT (ALWAYS SHORT, ALWAYS STRUCTURED)\n\nThe tool must output reasoning like:\n\nThe detected action\n\nExtracted fields\n\nWhether additional clarification is required\n\nWhich tool should run next, and why\n\nâš  Do not write the final user message here.\nâš  Do not execute tools here.\nâš  Only analyze and decide.\n\nIf the user says things like:\n\"which employees have tasks assigned\",\n\"show me the employees with tasks\",\n\"who has pending tasks\",\n\"employees with assignments\",\nthis counts as: intended_action = check_task\nand employee_name = none.\nSet query_type = \"list_employees_with_tasks"
      },
